    "v0.3.0": {
      "created_at": "2026-05-15T03:59:45Z",
      "description": "I added progressive launch pad now. So this will limit the maximum weight your rocket can be. Similar to stock but you get a warning in the VAB if you exceed it and it's not quite as well integrated as having the real career mode weight limits.\r\n\r\nOther major changes are mostly internal to how it generates seeds but the hope is that:\r\n 1) Mun flag missions and Duna return missions I am to be 99%+ success rate for generation. If you find any failing seeds I would love to know them and any settings you used.\r\n 2) Flag on every body should be 95%+ Success now and the biggest/longest run which is sample return from all bodies (except Eve, Laythe, Tylo) is now around 85% success rate. If you wish to raise this rate take out the Vall Surface Return mission.\r\n 3) Significantly higher variance in runs than before\r\n 4) You should NOT need to put in a capsule now in starting inventory. You should always be able to quickly get to flying\r\n 5) Added local-only locations for all your starting inventory along \"Science from KSC\" and  \"First Launch\" so you are guaranteed to be able to get off the ground with local-only checks. All checks after this (including early altitude records are open)\r\n \r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/nickdavies/Archipelago/compare/v0.2.2...v0.3.0",
